          "default": "<p><strong>What is it?</strong></p><p>A silver grid is a network of ultra-fine silver threads woven directly into the fabric at precise intervals, forming a continuous grid structure throughout the textile. Unlike silver ion treatments that are applied to the surface of a fabric and degrade with washing, a woven silver grid is a permanent part of the sheet's construction. It does not wash out, fade, or lose effectiveness over time.</p><p><strong>Why is it in the Jax Sheets?</strong></p><p>Silver is one of the most effective natural antimicrobial elements known, and in the Jax Sheets it works continuously to inhibit the growth of bacteria, fungi, and odor-causing microbes across the entire surface of the fabric. Because the silver is woven in rather than coated on, its protective properties remain consistent wash after wash and year after year. The result is a sheet that maintains a genuinely hygienic sleep surface over the long term, without relying on chemical treatments or needing to be replaced to stay effective.</p>"
